你肯定知道有我们想要什么
I'm sure you had a notion of what we're after.

24
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:02,800
我什么想法都没有
I didn't have any expectations.

25
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:05,270
我来是出于好奇
I just came because I was curious.

26
00:01:05,270 --> 00:01:08,160
那么让我来满足你的好奇心
Well, then let me satisfy your curiosity.

27
00:01:08,940 --> 00:01:11,310
如果你的书能伤到安德伍德夫妇
If your book can hurt the Underwoods,

28
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:13,980
我们要让它在竞选之前出版
we want it to be published before the election,

29
00:01:13,980 --> 00:01:16,200
并且要让它畅销
and we want it to be big.

30
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:17,990
戴娜·崔斯特  你认识吧
Dana Treister, do you know her?

31
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:20,150
《名利场》的编辑
The editor of Vanity Fair.

32
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:22,090
是的  她是我的密友
That's right. She's a close friend.

33
00:01:22,090 --> 00:01:24,540
还有本·格兰特  波利跳的创始人
And Ben Grant, founder of Pollyhop.

34
