但是  如果在《名利场》上大做广告...
but let's just say a big spread in Vanity Fair...

37
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:32,600
精彩的选节
Nice juicy excerpt,

38
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:36,420
托马斯·耶茨的深度报道  他的文学回归
profile on Thomas Yates, his literary comeback.

39
00:01:37,070 --> 00:01:41,140
我们本月上了封面  但下个月就可以是你
We're on the cover this month, but... next month it could be you.

40
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:43,710
我是最民主党的民主党
I'm on the Marxist side of Democrat.

41
00:01:45,060 --> 00:01:46,870
我为什么要帮助共和党
Why would I help a Republican?

42
00:01:46,910 --> 00:01:48,980
你是帮你自己  汤姆
You'd be helping yourself, Tom.

43
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:51,030
如果顺便帮助了我们
And if that helps us a little bit along the way,

44
00:01:51,030 --> 00:01:52,660
又有何不可呢
what's the harm in that?

45
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,590
俄亥俄参议员迪恩·奥斯汀
Senator Dean Austen of Ohio,

46
00:03:46,590 --> 00:03:49,030
领导层竞选伙伴的首选
the leadership's top choice for running mate.

47
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:50,390
供职国会12年
Twelve years in Congress,

48
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:52,280
能帮我们搞定这个重要摇摆州
helps us with a major swing state,

49
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:54,370
立场中立  极少树敌
middle of the road, very few enemies,

50
00:03:54,370 --> 00:03:58,150
他们最看重的  是全国步枪协会的老朋友
and most importantly to them, long-time friend of the NRA.

51
00:03:58,310 --> 00:04:01,310
缺点是  也是个中年白人
Now his shortcomings are he's another middle-aged white guy,

52
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:03,330
平庸无趣
underwhelming, unimaginative 

53
00:04:03,330 --> 00:04:05,400
而且是全国步枪协会的老朋友
and a long-time friend of the NRA.

54
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:08,740
这就是我对领导层这个选择的态度
So you can see how I feel about the leadership's choice.

55
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,050
参议员
Senator.

56
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:11,970
我很荣幸  总统先生
I'm honored, Mr. President.

57
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,740
我只有一个很大的顾虑
I just have one major reservation.

58
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:18,230
-克莱尔  -是的  先生
- Claire. - Yes, sir.

59
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:19,480
我只跟你说
Well, between you and me,

60
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:22,070
我都不确定这项枪支法案能否通过
I'm not even sure this gun bill is gonna pass.

61
00:04:22,070 --> 00:04:23,530
但如果要求我支持它
But if I'm being asked to support it,

62
00:04:23,530 --> 00:04:24,970
我很难做...
you know the sort of hot water--

63
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:26,760
是的  但是我需要你作为竞选伙伴
Yes, but I need you on the ticket

64
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:28,970
来平衡我们对待枪支的立场
to balance our stance on guns.

65
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:31,460
我们还要争取共和党的支持
We have to appeal to the Republicans as well.

66
