我不要求你支持法案
And look, I'm not asking you to get behind the bill,

67
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:36,310
只要不公然反对它就好
just not to publicly trash it.

68
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:38,390
我知道这对您很重要
I know this is an important issue to you.

69
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:39,760
确实很重要
It is important,

70
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,320
但不如一名经验丰富
but not as much as an experienced 

71
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:44,790
能拿下俄亥俄的领导人重要
leader who can deliver Ohio.

72
00:04:46,170 --> 00:04:47,800
那么我同意了  先生
Then consider me on board, sir.

73
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:53,170
我们不确定能在竞选前进入投票
We're not sure we can get this to the floor before the election.

74
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:54,910
我们有言在先
That's the deal we made.

75
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,300
奥斯汀的事如你们的愿  法案的事如我们的愿
You get Austen, we get the gun bill.

76
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:59,520
我们首先需要一份强势的参议院版本
We need a strong Senate version first,

77
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:02,440
这样才能避免两部无力的法案相互调和
so we don't have two weak bills going into reconciliation.

78
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:05,590
你们想要奥斯汀  就要让法案通过
You want Austen, you will make this bill a reality.

79
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:09,040
或者  我们可以重新考虑竞选伙伴的人选
Or, we can revisit the choice for running mate.

80
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:12,590
别  让我们想想办法吧
No... let us see what we can do.

81
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:13,870
我打给米切尔
I'll call Mitchell.

82
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:16,970
各位
Gentlemen,

83
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:19,250
有请未来的副总统
the future vice president.

84
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:21,010
-恭喜  迪恩  -非常感谢
- Congratulations, Dean. - Thank you very much.

85
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:22,770
-欢迎  -谢谢  安德伍德夫人
- Welcome. - Thank you. Mrs. Underwood.

86
00:05:22,770 --> 00:05:24,700
-认识你很高兴  -我也是
- Nice to meet you. - Very nice to meet you.

87
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,150
你们这边怎么样了
So, how's it going in here?

88
00:05:27,150 --> 00:05:30,370
我们算是达成共识了  是吧
Well, I think we're in alignment. Wouldn't you say?

89
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:33,150
这次会面很有成效
It's been a productive meeting.

90
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:35,520
来谈谈什么时候宣布吧
So, let's talk about when we should announce.

91
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:39,390
正式宣布之前  我得安抚一下
I, uh, I need to soften the blow to the NRA

92
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,490
全国步枪协会那边
before we go public. 

93
00:05:40,490 --> 00:05:42,610
一定要保守秘密
It's imperative we keep a lid on this.

94
00:05:42,610 --> 00:05:44,910
决不能提前泄露
No leaks until we're ready.

95
00:05:44,910 --> 00:05:46,770
只有我们四个知情
Just the four of us in this room.

96
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:49,000
当然还有克莱尔
And Claire, of course.

97
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,920
我有个简单采访要做
Well, I need to go do this quick interview.

98
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,130
米切尔那边的进展回头通知我
Um, let me know how it goes with Mitchell.

99
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,000
好了  你肯定有
All right, I'm sure you have some--

100
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,830
开着吧  屋里太憋了
Oh, leave that open. It gets so stuffy in here.

101
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,860
来讨论一下时间吧
Let's discuss the timing.

102
00:06:02,140 --> 00:06:03,700
是你还是第一夫人的主意
Was it you or the First Lady?

103
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:07,610
-完全是第一夫人  -她觉得可以把我争取过去
- First Lady all the way. - She thinks she can win me over?

104
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:09,590
她知道你下手肯定最重
She knows you'll hit harder than anyone else.

105
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:12,570
如果她能坚持到最后  那法案或许就能成
If she's still standing by the end, maybe the bill has sea legs.

106
00:06:13,490 --> 00:06:16,770
-凯特  -早上好  安德伍德夫人
- Kate. - Good morning, Mrs. Underwood.

107
00:06:16,770 --> 00:06:18,930
我们去罗斯福室谈吧
How about we talk in the Roosevelt Room?

108
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,980
国会的态度已经摇摆不定了
Support in the House is already wavering.

109
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:27,050
公众对枪的兴趣也在减少
The public's losing interest in guns.

110
00:06:27,110 --> 00:06:29,280
不等坐下再谈吗
Don't you want to wait until we sit down?

111
00:06:29,650 --> 00:06:32,260
我只有一小时的时间  得充分利用
Your staff only scheduled an hour. I want to make the most of it.

112
00:06:33,020 --> 00:06:34,560
被占了
Oh, it's being used.

113
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,260
换个地方吧
Let's find somewhere else.

114
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,270
凯特
Kate?

115
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:47,390
纵观历史  枪支改革的呼声潮起潮落
Well, historically, gun reform comes and goes in waves,

116
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:51,370
你也知道  我认为这次真的会不一样
as you know, so I believe this time, it can be truly different.

117
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:54,370
数据全部在这里进行过滤
All the data's filtered here, within these walls.

118
00:06:54,370 --> 00:06:56,440
分析师先初步过滤  最终
My analysts do a first pass, but ultimately,

119
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,500
由我做最后的筛选
I do the final round myself.

120
00:06:58,620 --> 00:07:00,510
我们最关心的是安全问题
Our biggest concern is security.

121
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:04,070
顶级防火墙  跟国安局总部的一样
Top-grade firewall, same as you guys use at NSA headquarters.

122
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:05,990
内部安全呢
What about internal security?

123
00:07:06,570 --> 00:07:08,810
只有我一个有全部权限
I'm the only one with full access.

124
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:10,380
你要是真发现了什么
So, if you do find anything,

125
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:13,210
怎么安全地转达给我们呢
how do you communicate that to us in a secure way?

126
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:14,280
亲自
In person.

127
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:17,440
我亲自去米德堡  或是你过来
I'll come to Fort Meade myself, or you come here.

128
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,880
{\an8}耻辱

129
