设备不带出去
No hardware leaves the premises.

130
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:23,010
能讲讲你们的过滤算法吗
Can you walk us through how the filtering algorithms work?

131
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:26,170
拿枪支为例吧
We'll take firearms, for instance.

132
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:28,670
从每个合法持有枪支的公民开始
If we start with everyone who legally owns a gun,

133
00:07:28,670 --> 00:07:31,590
通过手机追踪用户的地理规律
track geo-location patterns through their phones,

134
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:33,240
然后描绘一张
we start to put together a portrait

135
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:37,080
持有者生活  吃饭  购物  等等的地图
of where gun-owners live, eat, shop, everything.

136
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:41,190
根据这张图  我们预测未登记
From this, we predict everyone who might want a firearm,

137
00:07:41,190 --> 00:07:42,720
但有意向持枪的公民
but who isn't registered.

138
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:46,100
他们的行为模式很可能与合法持有者类似
They're likely to exhibit the same behavior as people who are.

139
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:49,730
这可以套用于对阿拉伯语感兴趣的人
You can use that for people who are interested in Arabic,

140
00:07:49,730 --> 00:07:52,110
想去中东的人
uh, wanna travel to the Middle East,

141
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:55,690
或是对美国政府绝望的人
who are disillusioned with the U.S. Government...

142
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,630
跟我们全球监控
So the same techniques that

143
00:08:02,630 --> 00:08:05,280
用的技术差不多
we're using for our international surveillance.

144
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,490
对
Yes... 

145
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:09,130
但先进得多
but far more advanced.

146
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:13,230
好了  转过来一点  康威夫人
Okay, turn a little bit towards me, Mrs. Conway.

147
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,120
好
Right.

148
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:20,330
你真美  汉娜
You look great, Hannah.

149
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:23,900
-那候选人呢  -别逼我吐槽  威尔
- What about the candidate? - Don't get me started, Will.

150
00:08:26,930 --> 00:08:29,490
-你真上镜  -我知道
- You're really photogenic. - I know.

151
00:08:32,610 --> 00:08:34,330
弗兰妮·华莱士  大四那年
Franny Wallace, senior year.

152
00:08:34,330 --> 00:08:37,370
-完全的金鱼食谱  -这些是特意摆这儿的吗
- The all-Goldfish diet. - Did you have these put here specially?

153
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:39,490
都是最棒的  亲爱的
We roll out the platinum carpet, darling.

154
00:08:39,790 --> 00:08:41,650
不知道弗兰妮现在在干什么
I wonder what Franny's up to now.

155
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:44,010
反正不是《名利场》的编辑
Hmm, not the Editor of Vanity Fair, I'll tell you that.

156
00:08:44,010 --> 00:08:45,930
或是即将当上第一夫人
Or about to be the First Lady.

157
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,490
我们真是成绩斐然啊  不是吗
Come a long way, haven't we?

158
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:53,030
是啊  威尔和我  很感谢你这么做...
Yeah, Will and I, um... Will and I appreciate your doing this.

159
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,310
又不是无偿的
It's not charity.

160
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:56,510
这一期有你们俩做封面肯定会卖疯了
This issue will sell like crazy with you two on the front.

161
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:58,770
我还是觉得应该报答你
Well, I feel like I should return the favor.

162
00:08:59,070 --> 00:09:00,680
让我在林肯卧室睡一晚
A night in the Lincoln Bedroom?

163
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:02,670
一篇报道
A story.

164
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,120
带副本来了吗
You have a copy for me?

165
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:20,890
这是一份摘要
An excerpt.

166
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:24,540
-我要整本书  -你只能拿到这个
- I need the whole book. - That's all you get.

167
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,180
康威也拿到了一样的东西
Conway got the same thing.

168
00:09:31,190 --> 00:09:34,070
-这是个错误  汤姆  -他们来找我的
- That was a mistake, Tom. - They came to me.

169
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:37,240
但他们不能发表...除非我允许
But they don't get to publish... without my approval.

170
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,850
你想要什么
So what do you want?

171
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,620
-一次会面  -为了什么
- A meeting. - For?

172
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,380
你只是个传话人  道格
You're just a messenger, Doug.

173
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,560
你听到我的话了
