00:09:55,620 --> 00:09:56,650
谢谢你请的咖啡
Thanks for the coffee.

176
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:03,050
安德伍德夫人  欢迎
Mrs. Underwood, welcome.

177
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:04,860
非常感谢您能来录制这段电话自动语音
Thank you so much for recording this robocall.

178
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,890
这对通过这项法案将有莫大的帮助
It'll go a long way in getting this bill passed.

179
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:10,220
谢谢你出色的工作
Well, thank you for all the extraordinary work you're doing.

180
00:10:10,590 --> 00:10:11,720
我要去哪里呢
Uh, where would you like me?

181
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,870
萨莉会带您去我们安排好进行录音的地方
Uh, Sally will show you where we set up for the recording.

182
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,410
这边请  安德伍德夫人
Right this way, Mrs. Underwood.

183
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:19,950
莉安
LeAnn...

184
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:27,550
那是什么
What is that?

185
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:30,220
姓名  电话号码  邮箱地址
Names, phone numbers, emails. 

186
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,330
25万个新目标
A quarter million fresh targets.

187
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:35,110
25万  你从哪里拿到的
A quarter million? Where'd you get this?

188
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:36,030
没写回信地址
No return address. 

189
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:38,060
是我们这里掌握的名字的50倍
It's 50 times the names that we have.

190
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:38,940
是真的吗
Is it legit? 

191
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:41,140
好像是  我们试着打了几通电话
Looks like it. We made sample calls.

192
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:45,120
你好  我是克莱尔·安德伍德
Hello, this is Claire Underwood.

193
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:48,480
我要坦白一件事...
I need to confess something...

194
00:10:48,990 --> 00:10:51,420
一件我并不引以为豪的事
something I'm not proud to confess.

195
00:10:52,050 --> 00:10:55,060
当我在医院里坐在我丈夫身旁时
When I was sitting beside my husband in the hospital...

196
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,010
我只考虑到我自己
all I thought about was me.

197
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:03,840
我的恐惧  一旦我失去他的痛苦
My fear. My pain if I was to lose him.

198
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,660
这是自私的
And it was selfish.

199
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,150
我没有考虑到其他人
I-- I wasn't thinking about everyone else

200
00:11:09,150 --> 00:11:11,420
那些曾经历同样的恐惧和痛苦的人
who had gone through that fear and pain,

201
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:13,450
那些曾坐在我所坐的位置上
who had to sit where I was sitting

202
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:18,530
他们所爱的人被不该持有枪支的人射伤的人
because a loved one was shot by someone who shouldn't have a gun.

203
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:23,800
我感到羞愧  因为我从未对此做过什么
I'm ashamed because I've never done anything about it.

204
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:28,150
我为本可拯救的那么多生命而羞愧
I'm ashamed of how many lives we could've saved.

205
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:32,100
那么多家庭本可避免这样的痛苦
How many families we could've kept from suffering.

206
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:37,070
我们都应该感到羞愧  我们每一个人
We should all be ashamed, every one of us,

207
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:40,050
因为我们所有人都有责任
because the blood is on all of our hands,

208
00:11:40,050 --> 00:11:43,540
而什么都不做就等同于扣动扳机
and doing nothing is the same as pulling a trigger.

209
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:46,980
我们得做点什么
We need to do something.

210
00:11:53,570 --> 00:11:56,270
那就是  修改法律
And that means changing the law.

211
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,480
奥斯汀参议员办公室
Senator Austen's office.

212
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:47,790
从下午开始已经接到五百多个电话了
More than 500 since this afternoon. 

213
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,950
单单我们区吗
From our district?

214
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:49,570
我们都算少的
We have it light. 

215
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:52,420
我听说其他办公室接到一千多个电话
I'm hearing that other offices have gotten over a thousand.

216
00:12:52,690 --> 00:12:55,610
奥斯汀参议员办公室  我会转达
Senator Austen's office. I will take a message.

217
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,070
弗兰西斯
Francis.

218
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,210
你真的不该这么做
You really shouldn't.

219
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:06,220
抽一根不会死的
Oh, one won't kill me.

220
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,190
你读完了吗
Did you finish it?

221
00:13:13,810 --> 00:13:14,570
嗯
Yeah.

222
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:19,340
有一个地方吸引了我
One part really caught my eye.

223
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:25,990
"一条裂缝在他们之间蔓延开来
"A chasm opened up between them,

224
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:29,710
那是一条不到九米宽的走廊
a hallway less than ten yards wide.

225
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:32,720
但它就像有两千公里那么长
But it might as well have been a thousand miles.

226
00:13:33,290 --> 00:13:35,060
这是一片布置精致的无人之地
A well-appointed no man's land

227
00:13:35,070 --> 00:13:39,150
丝绒地毯和高悬的天花板隔开了两间卧房
with a plush carpet and high ceiling between two bedrooms.

228
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:42,620
卧房里住着两个世纪的鬼魂
In it were two centuries of ghosts,

229
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:45,550
之前所有的总统和第一夫人
all the Presidents and First Ladies before them.

230
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:49,600
还有他们婚姻的鬼魂
But also the ghost... of their marriage.

231
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:53,920
30年的斗争  让他们的心都死了
A thirty years' war that left them both dead inside

232
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:56,960
两人之间也是一片荒原"
and this dead space between them."

233
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,250
真有洞察力
He's perceptive.

234
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:05,600
简直可怕
Uncanny.

235
00:14:11,250 --> 00:14:14,160
那已经不是我们了  已经变了
Well, it's not who we are. Not anymore.

236
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:19,380
就算是假的  人民还是愿意相信是真的
People will want to believe it's true even if it's false.

237
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:23,380
你觉得他想得到什么
What do you think it is he wants to accomplish?

238
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:30,050
我叫你辞职之后有一晚他来过
He came here one night, after I'd asked you to resign.

239
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:33,110
他说他很着迷
He said he was obsessed.

240
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:36,510
也许他还想接着写
Or maybe he wants back in.

241
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,470
你对他有感情
You felt something for him.

242
00:14:49,290 --> 00:14:50,770
有那么一刻吧
Maybe for a moment.

243
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,510
-你呢  -没有
- Did you? - No, I don't think so.

244
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:02,650
我感觉
I felt...

245
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:07,210
我感觉他看得到我
I felt like he saw me.

246
00:15:11,100 --> 00:15:12,100
我也是
Me, too.

247
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:37,580
巴恩斯先生
Mr. Barnes.

248
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:41,870
你打过电话之后  我就一直在想
I couldn't stop thinking, since you called...

249
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,320
佐伊的事
about Zoe.

250
00:15:45,610 --> 00:15:48,860
-我想要个答复  -我也是
- I guess I want answers. - That-- That's what I want, too.

251
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:54,850
-你想知道什么  -他们有过恋情吗
- What is it you want to know? - Was there... a relationship?

252
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:57,120
她和安德伍德
With Underwood?

253
00:15:59,810 --> 00:16:03,370
她17岁时  去上学之前
When she was 17, just before she went off to school...

254
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,560
她发现我有外遇
she found out I was having an affair.

255
00:16:08,310 --> 00:16:10,680
药物公司的销售代表
Sales rep, some drug company.

256
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:13,660
是个金发妞
Blonde. You know.

257
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:17,280
这是非正式的谈话吧
This isn't, you know, on the record.

258
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:22,610
当然   你不想公开就不公开
No... No, not if you don't want it to be.

259
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,170
你说她发现了
You said she found out.

260
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:34,100
她给我三天时间向她妈妈坦白  不然就
She gave me three days to tell her mother, or she would...

261
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,630
抱歉  喝了点酒
I'm sorry, I had a few drinks.

262
00:16:41,770 --> 00:16:44,780
-你告诉她了吗  -告诉了
- Did you tell her? - Yeah, I told her.

263
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,050
我们离婚了
We split up.

264
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:50,180
那之后佐伊就不怎么理我了
Zoe didn't talk to me much after that.

265
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,980
我不清楚安德伍德的事
I don't know anything about Underwood.

266
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:57,850
她肯定不会告诉我
I'm the last person she would've told.

267
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:07,060
我真希望我当初  能多尽点力
I wish I would've... made more of an effort...

268
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:10,200
跟她沟通
to reach out to her.

269
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,770
你在开车吗  巴恩斯先生
Are you driving, Mr. Barnes?

270
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:14,950
在
Yeah.

271
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:19,530
-我快到家了  -你该停车
- I'm almost home. - You should pull over.

272
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,640
你查到什么了吗
Did you find out anything?

273
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:24,240
可以告诉我的事
Anything you can tell me?

274
00:17:25,190 --> 00:17:27,770
她在《先驱报》没几个朋友
She didn't have a lot of friends at the Herald.

275
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:31,250
就我的了解
Um, from what I can gather,

276
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:33,260
她就没有亲密的朋友
she didn't have any close friends at all.

277
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:36,790
我跟她邻里的人谈过
I spoke to some people in her neighborhood...

278
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:40,280
但还没什么发现
but nothing so far.

279
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:42,860
你会告诉我吗
Will you?

280
00:17:44,350 --> 00:17:46,400
-如果查到  -当然
- If you... - Yeah, of course, of course.

281
00:17:47,550 --> 00:17:49,020
如果你想起了什么
If you think of anything...

282
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:49,880
当然
Yeah.

283
00:17:57,650 --> 00:18:01,510
{\an8}枪支  阴谋和白宫

284
00:18:16,060 --> 00:18:17,560
那你当时去那儿干什么
Then what were you doing there?

285
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,360
我去白宫开会
If I do a meeting at the White House,

286
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:21,470
还需要理由吗  茱莉亚
I don't have to explain myself, Julia.

287
00:18:21,470 --> 00:18:23,040
法案可能会通过
This bill might pass.

288
00:18:23,630 --> 00:18:26,130
-我知道  -你在帮他们吗
- I realize that. - Are you helping them?

289
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:28,370
当然没有
Absolutely not.

290
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:38,410
-茱莉亚  -安德伍德夫人
- Julia. - Mrs. Underwood.

291
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:41,170
抱歉  我该跟你握手  但我刚跑步回来
Sorry, I'd shake your hand, but I just got back from a run.

292
00:18:41,170 --> 00:18:42,120
我想说
Listen, I wanted to say,

293
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:44,180
我知道上次的会面不太顺利
I know our meeting last time didn't go very well,

294
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:46,080
那是怪我  我的话太无礼了
and that's on me. It was rude, what I said,

295
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:48,280
希望你接受我的道歉
and I hope you'll accept my apology.

296
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:50,320
请坐吧
Have a seat, please.

297
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,840
你以前进过宅邸吗
You ever been in the residence before?

298
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:59,440
套近乎我也不会支持你的
The personal touch isn't going to bring me on board.

299
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:01,740
给国会打几万个电话也没用
Neither will a few thousand calls to Congress.

300
00:19:01,740 --> 00:19:04,790
不到24小时  8.4万个
84,000 in less than 24 hours.

301
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:06,920
先不谈那个
But let's put that aside for a moment

302
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:09,220
-来说说你的好朋友  -谁
- and talk about your good friend. - Who?

303
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:12,880
-奥斯汀参议员  -他说了  竞选伙伴
- Senator Austen. - He told me. Running mate.

304
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:14,720
不只是竞选伙伴
Oh, not just running mate.

305
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:17,830
你说我不必支持这个法案的
You said I wouldn't have to support this bill.

306
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:19,920
是啊  但是计划赶不上变化  迪恩
Yes, but a lot can change in a day, Dean.

307
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:23,120
没想到会有这么大的呼声
We had no idea there'd be this sort of groundswell.

308
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,210
就因为跟你共处一室
Julia Melman was all over

309
00:19:24,210 --> 00:19:27,000
茱莉亚·梅尔曼就对我逼问个不停
my ass even for being in the same room as you.

310
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,370
你告诉她了吗
Did you tell her?

311
00:19:29,130 --> 00:19:31,110
-没办法  -天哪  迪恩
- I had to. - Christ, Dean...

312
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:32,670
不然就要树个死敌
It was that, or make an enemy for life.

313
00:19:32,670 --> 00:19:34,410
她很生气  但应该能想明白
She's upset, but I think she'll come around,

314
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:35,520
除非你逼我支持
unless you make me endorse

315
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,430
堵上枪展和网络卖枪的漏洞
closing the gun show and Internet loopholes.

316
00:19:37,430 --> 00:19:39,010
那她可就要爆发了
Then she'll go ballistic.

317
00:19:39,110 --> 00:19:41,960
迪恩不会的  我们为他竞选出资上百万
Dean wouldn't do that. We've poured millions into his campaigns.

318
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:43,750
现在他不需要你了
And now he doesn't need you anymore.

319
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:46,780
你是要威胁我吗  逼我们让步
Are you trying to intimidate me? To get us to back down?

320
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:48,530
不  我有个提议
No, I have an offer.

321
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:51,810
民主党想拿下俄亥俄不容易
Ohio's a tough state for Democrats. 

322
00:19:51,810 --> 00:19:53,240
茱莉亚一直对我很好
Julia's been very good to me.

323
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,680
我懂  忠诚是很重要
Loyalty's important, I understand,

324
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:58,520
但你现在必须忠于我
but your loyalty has to be with me now.

325
00:19:58,610 --> 00:19:59,870
我做不到
I just can't do it.

326
00:20:00,630 --> 00:20:02,040
好吧  那就不公布了
All right, then we'll cancel the announcement.

327
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,410
我另找个竞选伙伴好了
I'll find someone else to be my running mate.

328
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:06,590
不  我  我没法支持这项法案
No, I mean, I... I just can't support this bill.

329
00:20:06,650 --> 00:20:09,710
但是现在  两件事绑在一起了
Oh, but you see, the two go hand in hand now.

330
00:20:09,910 --> 00:20:12,470
你答应不答应
So, are you on the ticket or not?

331
00:20:13,330 --> 00:20:16,710
如果众议院通过  参议院不通过呢
What if the gun bill passes in the House, but not the Senate?

332
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,470
你要什么回报
In return for what?

333
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:21,970
你说服参议员退出
You convince the senator to pull out.

334
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:25,880
领导层想要他  我们也配合了他们
Now, the leadership wants him, and we've played nice,

335
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:28,440
但我和总统想要的是凯茜·杜兰特
but the president and I want Cathy Durant.

336
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:30,270
她参选要更有希望
She's a much stronger candidate.

337
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,480
你愿放弃自己的法案吗
You're willing to abandon your own bill?

338
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:35,010
要在击败康威和击败你之间选
If it's means beating Conway or beating you,

339
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:36,650
多容易选啊
that's not a hard choice.

340
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:38,950
我已经告诉迪恩
I already told Dean that

341
00:20:38,950 --> 00:20:40,760
他做竞选伙伴我可以接受
I could live with him being running mate.

342
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,170
我怎么能反悔
How do I backtrack?

343
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,470
明天看新闻吧
Just watch the news tomorrow.

344
00:20:44,490 --> 00:20:46,040
你做了正确的选择
You made the right choice.

345
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,930
-但愿吧  -别但愿  就是
- I hope so. - Well, don't hope so, know so.

346
00:20:47,930 --> 00:20:51,860
我会让赛斯给你一份讲稿
And I'll have Seth send you a copy of the speech.

347
00:20:53,190 --> 00:20:54,800
可以送参议员出去了  谢谢
You can show the senator out now, thank you.

348
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,760
是  先生
